The paper discusses using deep neural networks for code search using natural language, which involves information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Therefore, cs.IR and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of supervised and unsupervised techniques for learning embeddings, which falls under machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.LG and cs.AI likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper evaluates the effectiveness of different network designs for code search, which is related to software engineering (SE), making cs.SE a possible sub-category.
